rComments: What a quack stay away from this guy mean spirited at times, couldn't care less about his class..
Very eloquent lecturer; provides ample support (if one so desires); has high expectations of his students. Prof. Taylor nurtured my interest in African Canadian history

Did not like his lectures, he read off the text book. He was cold towards his students and didn't help them in any way. He was boring and didn't seem to really like people in general. My advice is do not take any of his courses.

He had nothing to offer and I couldn't wait for the class to end.  He teaches a subject that is rare to find in Canadian universities (history of African-Canadians...struggles, accomplishments etc) and he should have made it more appealing.  He is a snobby showoff and needs to learn how to teach and interact with students a little better.

Seemed unprepared and uninterested in his own class. His lectures were useless as he read from the assigned reading or rambled most of the time. He would have trouble filling the two hours of lecture a week, and left the moment it ended. He never explained what he wanted from assignments, yet graded extremely harshly. Avoid at all costs.

He had a class participation mark but never really encouraged much discussion and would end the class early. His expectations on assignments were unclear and ambiguous. Lectures consisted of a lot of repeated info from the readings and he was vulgar. All in all, he was dull and uninspiring, and one of the worst professors I ever had.
Repeats.  Repeats.  Repeats.  Poorly prepared.  Autocratic.

All this guy does is read bits and pieces from the assigned readings.  Going to his boring classes is a waste of time.  If you're interested in learning about history, check out the other profs teaching this fascinating subject.
Great prof! Super helpful, very kind and wiling to go the extra mile for all of his undergraduate students!

Sheldon Taylor does not know how to teach. He reads directly from the text book with no outside materials. He is not a good Professor. You can still pass the course just by reading the text book, as his lectures are useless.
Repeats himself ALOT. Doesn't say much other than repeating the readings. But he's very nice and helpful.
Good prof.  Lectures are repetitive to the required reading.
If you have have chance to study with Prof. Taylor you would do well to avail yourself of the opportunity.  His TA Dr. Deb Neill is really super too!

He's a really good prof! He is smart, modern, funny, quick-witted, and mean to people who are rude. He has a passion for the issue and doesn't buy into the emotion testimony that often follows issue related to Caribbean History. Haven't recieved any mark yet, so we'll see...

Prof. Taylor is a bit batty-meaning disorganized-and although it can be frustrating I mostly mean it fondly.  Very kind, very supportive and helpful.  Very passionate about his subject. Can over-intellecutualize, but that's okay. Tough marker!  However, very receptive to students.
Teaches Caribbean history.  Today was my first day so I don't have much to say about him yet.
